'''Bankers' hours''' refers to the period between 10am and 3pm.

For many years these were the traditional opening hours of a [[Bank]]. Sometimes used to imply that someone has an easy job in that it is a short [[working day]]. However this could be deemed unwarranted as bank staff worked several hours outside of 10am and 3pm - typically with [[ledger]]s - doing work that is nowadays done by computers.
